    "number": 13626,
    "state": "closed",
    "locked": false,
    "title": "[Model][Speculative Decoding] Expand DeepSeek MTP code to support k > n_predict",
    "user": {
      "login": "benchislett",
      "id": 31750416,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMxNzUwNDE2",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/31750416?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/benchislett",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/benchislett/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "This PR extends the DeepSeek MTP implementation such that the number of speculative tokens may be greater than the number of prediction modules. In these such cases, the layers are reused by feeding the hidden states from one into the next. \n\nThis will also fix a few issues with the original implementation that would not have been able to handle `k > 1`:\n- Disable `TP1DraftModelRunner` usage. As I understand DeepSeek MLA is not compatible with multi-step at all, so this pathway would not be compatible with `k > 1`. I do not expect there would be any benefits to using this path for `k=1`.\n- Enable hidden states forwarding in the fallback model-runner case, so that either code path can be used for EAGLE-style speculative decoding. I believe this will enable `TP > 1` on all EAGLE models, but I have not tested this claim beyond MTP.\n\nBelow are benchmark results on 8xH200 with sample requests from ShareGPT:\n\n| Max Concurrency | Baseline TPOT | k=1 TPOT | k=2 TPOT | k=3 TPOT |\n|-----------------|---------------|----------|----------|----------|\n| 1               | 22.97ms       | 17.31ms  | 14.98ms  | 14.30ms  |\n| 2               | 27.45ms       | 17.50ms  | 16.17ms  | 16.72ms  |\n| 4               | 29.86ms       | 22.62ms  | 20.53ms  | 25.30ms  |\n| 8               | 35.09ms       | 38.43ms  | 25.25ms  | 32.39ms  |\n\nWith the following reported acceptance rates: 83% for k=1, 72% for k=2, 61% for k=3.\n\nUntil additional MTP module weights are released, using this implementation with `k=2` gives the best performance from my testing. \n\n\n",
    "created_at": "2025-02-20T19:02:24Z",
